		<title>Press Release: Stage for the people by The PPL</title>
		<link>http://theppl.us/blog/731</link>
		<comments>http://theppl.us/blog/731#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 25 Jun 2012 13:52:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Desiree Kane</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Press Releases]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://theppl.us/?p=731</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Stage for the people by The PPL Public is invited to submit ideas for stage presentations during the Democratic National Convention Charlotte, N.C. &#8211; The PPL, in an innovative move to democratize its stage, requests topic submissions for their stage during the Democratic National Convention.  The submissions will be accepted through July 3 and announced in [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>
<p style="text-align: center;" dir="ltr"><strong>Stage for the people by The PPL</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;" dir="ltr"><em><strong>Public is invited to submit ideas for stage presentations during the Democratic National Convention</strong></em></p>
<p><em><strong>Charlotte, N.C</strong></em>. &#8211; The PPL, in an innovative move to democratize its stage, requests topic submissions for their stage during the Democratic National Convention.  The submissions will be accepted through July 3 and announced in early August.  In the spirit of extending the concept of an open and accessible convention experience for the community, The PPL’s stage is an opportunity for convention attendees to present and discuss the topics and issues through their own lens.</p>
</div>
<div>&#8220;The PPL&#8217;s curated conversations, which will involve thought and action leaders from our community and beyond, is way to make it possible for visiting independent media professionals to plug into important topics surrounding the DNC including ideological, economic, environmental, and social agendas.&#8221; Says Candice Langston, Stage Production Lead.</div>
<div></div>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-735" style="border-style: initial; border-color: initial; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; border-width: 0px;" title="Screen Shot 2012-06-06 at 2.58.57 PM" src="http://theppl.us/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Screen-Shot-2012-06-06-at-2.58.57-PM1-1024x574.png" alt="" width="1024" height="574" /></p>
<div>Example themes and topics sought after include:</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li>the future of civic, voter, and/or engagement</li>
<li>dialogue vs. diatribe</li>
<li>the future of social media</li>
<li>open forum engagement</li>
<li>the economic divide</li>
<li>bridging ideological gaps</li>
<li>faith-based discrimination</li>
<li>exploring economic and social agendas</li>
<li>environmental sustainability</li>
<li>connecting the dots</li>
<li>healthcare reform</li>
<li>interconnectedness</li>
<li>higher education reform</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div><strong>Submission deadline is July 3, 11:59PM.</strong></div>
<div></div>
<div>Voting on suggested topics will begin after July 3rd and announced in early August.<strong><strong><br />
</strong></strong></div>
<div>
<p dir="ltr">The PPL is a non-partisan grassroots initiative to promote healthy, productive public discourse by providing work space and resources for bloggers and independent media in Charlotte during the DNC. Although we welcome all media personnel, flights and accommodations will not be paid for by The PPL, however we will help with any questions. For more information, visit <a href="http://theppl.us">http://theppl.us</a> or watch the video below:</p>
<p><object width="560" height="315" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/LX2l4BTQDhk?version=3&amp;hl=en_US" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed width="560" height="315" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/LX2l4BTQDhk?version=3&amp;hl=en_US" allowFullScreen="true" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" /></object><br />
###</p>
</div>
